tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and increased alkaline phosphatase, which may indicate possible hepatobiliary or bone involvement. HDL cholesterol is slightly below normal, representing increased cardiovascular risk. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and proteins, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal and hepatic status.
